        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Bank, Southampton,</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Ap 4 <hi rend="print">18</hi>77</date>
                    <salute>My dear Father,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I send M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Fox’s reply which I fancy will be sufficient for you.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> I have just heard from the lawyer. If you will send me a cheque (payable to me) for £477— it settle the payment of the land.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>I am paying him today.</p>
<p>I hope the bothering Spottiswoode did not keep you long in a state of waiting.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>Your affect son | W E. Darwin</p>
<p>P.S. the lawyer’s Bill will come afterwards</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="annotations">
                <note><hi rend="italic">End of letter</hi>: ‘House [‘30’ <hi rend="italic">pencil del blue crayon</hi>] t’ <hi rend="italic">pencil</hi>; ‘40’ <hi rend="italic">blue crayon</hi></note>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">William enclosed a <ref target="./DCP-LETT-10923.xml" resp="#automat" cert="medium">letter from William Darwin Fox of 3 April [1877]</ref>. Fox had replied to a query from CD on <hi rend="italic">Pulmonaria</hi> (the genus of lungworts; see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-10923.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from W. D. Fox, 3 April [1877]</ref> and n. 2).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD recorded a payment of £477 on 5 April 1877 with the notation ‘W. E. Darwin for Beesby Farm (Invested)’ in his Account books–banking account (Down House MS). CD had owned Beesby Farm in Lincolnshire since 1845 (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 3). The lawyer has not been identified.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">The reference to ‘the bothering Spottiswoode’ (<ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4500.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">William Spottiswoode</ref>) has not been identified.</note>
        </div>        
            
